title: ‘There is hope’: Australia welcomes Trump’s 20-point peace plan for Gaza
summary: Australian Prime Minister Anthony Albanese supports the commitment to exclude Hamas from future governance in Gaza. He is calling on Hamas to agree to the proposed terms for peace. Albanese's stance highlights the international community's desire for stability in the region.

title: Raya won $93,000 in a class action after she was strip-searched by police and forced to remove her tampon
summary: Police acknowledged they unlawfully strip-searched Raya Meredith at the 2018 Splendour in the Grass festival. They also retracted all witnesses ahead of the court hearing. This admission highlights serious concerns regarding police procedures and accountability.

title: Dolphins beat sloppy Jets but Tyreek Hill sustains probable season-ending injury
summary: Miami's Darren Waller made a strong comeback in his first NFL game in nearly two years, scoring two touchdown catches. However, the Dolphins' victory was overshadowed by injuries. Despite Waller's performance, the team's health concerns loomed large.

title: Optus boss ‘has a lot of work to do’, Anika Wells says after meeting telco and Singtel in wake of triple-zero outages
summary: The Minister has urged the parent company to implement an external review process aimed at improving the reliability of emergency calls in Australia. This initiative is part of efforts to rebuild public trust in the emergency response system. The move comes in response to growing concerns over the effectiveness of current services.
